---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';

const questions = [
  ['What is actually profitable?', 'See product and customer performance without guessing from revenue alone.'],
  ['What is changing?', 'Spot movement in sales, repeat purchases, cash pressure, and inventory before it becomes a surprise.'],
  ['Where should I focus?', 'Use a small number of clear views instead of chasing reports across disconnected tools.'],
];
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Kilo for business owners"
  description="Connect business systems and see sales, cash, products, and customers in one place."
>
  <section class="hero">
    <p class="eyebrow">For owner-operators</p>
    <h1>See your whole business in one place without learning data jargon.</h1>
    <p class="lede">
      Connect the tools you already use. Get a clear view of sales, cash,
      products, and customers without hiring a data team first.
    </p>
    <div class="actions">
      <a class="button" href="mailto:hello@example.com">See your business</a>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section section-muted split">
    <div>
      <p class="eyebrow">The problem</p>
      <h2>Your systems know what is happening. They just do not agree with each other.</h2>
      <p>
        Sales are in one place. Accounts are in another. Inventory, margin, cash,
        and repeat customers are hard to see together. Decisions get made from
        partial views.
      </p>
      <p>Kilo connects the pieces and gives you a usable business picture without asking you to understand warehouse modelling.</p>
    </div>
    <aside class="note">
      <h3>You should not need to know</h3>
      <p>Star schemas, ETL, joins, keys, lineage, marts, staging tables, or dbt.</p>
      <h3>You should be able to know</h3>
      <p>Which products make money, which customers come back, what changed this month, and whether the next order is affordable.</p>
    </aside>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <p class="eyebrow">Useful questions</p>
    <h2>Answers you can act on.</h2>
    <div class="item-grid item-grid-three">
      {questions.map(([title, text]) => (
        <article>
          <h3>{title}</h3>
          <p>{text}</p>
        </article>
      ))}
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section cta">
    <p class="eyebrow">First step</p>
    <h2>Start with two systems.</h2>
    <p>Connect the two systems that hold the most important parts of the business, then check whether the picture is useful.</p>
    <a class="button" href="mailto:hello@example.com">See your business</a>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
